{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s003", "order": 3, "text": "The Morse message queue intermittently stalls during local Daylight Saving Time (DST) transitions, specifically when clocks advance from 02:00 to 03:00.", "char_start": 40, "char_end": 192, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 25}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s004", "order": 4, "text": "This occurs because local timestamping introduces a non-monotonic jump, causing messages with timestamps during the skipped hour to appear out of order or invalid.", "char_start": 193, "char_end": 356, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 26}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s005", "order": 5, "text": "As a result, the queue halts processing until manual intervention or timeout recovery, disrupting time-critical telemetry operations.", "char_start": 357, "char_end": 490, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 22}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s006", "order": 6, "text": "**Fix**", "char_start": 492, "char_end": 499, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 3}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s007", "order": 7, "text": "All message timestamps will be converted to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) at the point of queue insertion, eliminating reliance on system-local time.", "char_start": 502, "char_end": 654, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 28}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s008", "order": 8, "text": "A DST flag will be added to the message header for diagnostic transparency, allowing downstream systems to detect whether the message originated during a DST transition.", "char_start": 655, "char_end": 824, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 28}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s009", "order": 9, "text": "This ensures temporal consistency across all regions and avoids ambiguity during clock changes.", "char_start": 825, "char_end": 920, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 14}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s010", "order": 10, "text": "**Test**", "char_start": 922, "char_end": 930, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 3}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s011", "order": 11, "text": "Implement a simulation that toggles the system clock across a DST boundary (02:00 â†’ 03:00) in a controlled environment.", "char_start": 933, "char_end": 1052, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 22}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s012", "order": 12, "text": "Enqueue messages at 01:59:59, 02:00:00 (skipped), and 03:00:01.", "char_start": 1053, "char_end": 1116, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 13}
{"doc_id": "d578a973-641c-54d3-af31-94b0c193f417", "req_id": "REQ-166", "sent_id": "REQ-166::s013", "order": 13, "text": "Verify that messages are timestamped in UTC without interruption, and the queue processes all entries in chronological order.", "char_start": 1117, "char_end": 1242, "splitter": "stanza", "token_count": 20}
